# Table of Contents

*Configurable defaults: Every number in this document is a confirmed default value from Rania. All values are stored in the database and configurable by any salon owner at any time without code changes. Nothing is hardcoded in the application. Currency is USD at launch.*

# 1. Platform Vision

B-Edge is a beauty booking platform built for Lebanon and the MENA region. It is an open platform where any salon, studio, or independent artist can register, onboard their team, define their services and pricing, and accept bookings online.

Rania is the launch partner and the most complex case: multi-artist, two stores across two cities, cross-city travel buffers, bridal packages, home visits, international travel, courses, flexible pricing, discounts, and a product store. If B-Edge works for Rania, it works for every simpler salon in the region.

| **Principle** | **Detail** | **Industry reference** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Open platform | Any salon or independent artist in Lebanon and MENA can register. | Fresha, Vagaro open marketplace model |
| Rania as benchmark | Rania is the hardest case. Every feature designed for her complexity first. | B-Edge unique positioning |
| Configurable by design | Every rule, fee, and time window configurable per salon. Nothing hardcoded. | Vagaro, Zenoti configurable model |
| Custom services | Every salon can add custom services beyond the platform catalogue. No approval needed. | Vagaro, Square custom service model |
| Arabic-first | Arabic RTL support from day one. WhatsApp as primary communication channel. | B-Edge MENA differentiator. No competitor does this properly. |
| Build once, activate later | All services defined in DB at launch. Salons activate what they offer. | B-Edge unique feature |
| Currency | USD only at launch. Multi-currency in Phase 3 MENA expansion. | Industry standard for Lebanese market |

# 2. Launch Partner

Rania is a beauty artist based in Lebanon with 400,000 Instagram followers and two physical studios in Beirut Downtown and Tripoli. She leads a team of specialist artists covering makeup, hair, and skincare. She also runs a product store on Instagram selling makeup and hair products.

Rania represents the hardest scheduling and pricing scenario on the platform. All features are validated against her requirements first.

# 3. Entity Relationships and Roles

## 3.1 Platform Hierarchy

| **Level** | **Entity** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Platform (B-Edge) | The platform. Contains all salons and independent artists. |
| 2 | Salon | A business entity. One owner, one or more stores, a team of staff. Example: Rania Studio. |
| 2 | Independent artist | An artist with no salon. Their profile is their own store. No team. |
| 3 | Store | A physical location belonging to a salon. Example: Rania Studio Beirut. |
| 3 | Staff | Artists, assistants, managers, and receptionists belonging to a salon. |
| 3 | Product store | Optional online store per salon. Sells physical products. Cash on delivery at launch. |
| 4 | Customer | Any person who books a service or orders a product. |

## 3.2 Staff Roles and Permissions

Based on Fresha 5-level permission model and GlossGenius role-based access control. Every staff member has their own login. Credentials are never shared.

| **Role** | **Rania team** | **Can do** | **Cannot do** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Owner | Rania | Everything. Full access for the salon. | Nothing restricted. |
| Manager | Future hire | Manage staff, bookings, pricing, reports for their store. | Delete salon, change billing, access other store financials. |
| Receptionist | Future hire | Manage bookings, customers, approvals, refund queue. | Change pricing, manage staff, view financial reports. |
| Artist | Hadia, Mirvat, Hair Girl 1, Hair Girl 2 | Own calendar, own services, own bookings only. | See other artists revenue, change store settings. |
| Assistant | Makeup assistant | View own schedule only. | Manage anything. |

*Note: Rania currently fills Owner, Manager, and Receptionist simultaneously. These roles exist for when she hires dedicated staff.*

## 3.3 Artist Onboarding

- Any artist can register and create a profile. Linked to a salon or standalone.

- No approval required from B-Edge platform. Artists go live after completing onboarding.

- Salon owner invites staff. Staff creates their own account linked to the salon.

- During onboarding the artist sets: services, pricing, availability, deposit amounts, travel buffers.

- All values are configurable after onboarding. Artist updates pricing at any time.

