# 7. Deposit and Cancellation Policy

## 7.1 Deposit Rules

| **Booking type** | **Rania deposit default** | **Configurable** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| In-store booking | $50 | Yes per artist |
| Home visit inside Lebanon | $500 | Yes per artist |
| Travel outside Lebanon | $500 (part of $2,000 fee) | Yes per artist |
| Private course | Configurable | Yes per artist |
| Class course | Configurable | Yes per artist |

*Default value: Deposit deadline: 48 hours before appointment. Auto-cancels if unpaid. Slot released.. Configurable per salon.*

*Default value: Payment methods: Wish Money (primary), cash (secondary), bank transfer (outside Lebanon).. Configurable per salon.*

## 7.2 Deposit Verification

Deposit verification is manual at launch. Rania confirms payment on her Wish Money account and marks the deposit as received in her dashboard. The system tracks verification status.

| **Verification step** | **Who** | **System action** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Customer sends deposit via Wish Money | Customer | No system action. Customer optionally notes transaction reference in special requests field. |
| Rania checks her Wish Money account | Rania | No system action. |
| Rania marks deposit received in dashboard | Rania | Booking status changes from approved to deposit_paid. Customer notified. |

*Note: Phase 3: Wish Money or payment gateway API integration will automate deposit verification.*

## 7.3 Cancellation Policy

| **Scenario** | **Deposit outcome** | **System action** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Customer cancels more than 24 hours before | Returned to customer | Booking marked refund_due. Artist notified. Customer sees refund pending. |
| Customer cancels less than 24 hours before | Forfeited | Booking cancelled. Deposit kept. Customer notified. |
| Customer no-show | Forfeited | Artist marks no-show. Deposit kept. Slot freed. |
| Artist cancels or reschedules | Returned to customer in full | Booking marked refund_due. Artist notified. Customer sees refund pending. |
| Deposit deadline passed (48h before appointment) | No deposit. Slot released. | Booking auto-expires. Waitlist triggered. |

*Default value: Cancellation window: 24 hours before appointment.. Configurable per salon.*

- Refund is manual. Rania transfers via Wish Money. System tracks: refund_due, refund_completed, refund_amount, refunded_at.

- Customer sees refund status in their profile.

- Phase 3: automated refunds via payment gateway.

# 8. Booking Flow

## 8.1 Booking State Machine

| **Status** | **Meaning** | **Triggered by** | **Next states** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| held | Slot reserved during checkout. 10 minutes. First-write-wins at DB level via GIST constraint. | Customer begins booking form. | pending, released |
| released | Hold expired. Slot freed. | Background job after 10 minutes. | Final state. |
| pending | Customer submitted. Awaiting artist review. | Customer completes booking form. | approved, cancelled |
| approved | Artist approved. Awaiting deposit. Deadline: 48 hours before appointment. | Artist approves in dashboard. | deposit_paid, expired, cancelled |
| deposit_paid | Deposit received. Booking confirmed. | Artist marks deposit received. | completed, no_show, cancelled |
| completed | Appointment done. | Artist marks completed. | Final state. |
| cancelled | Cancelled by customer or artist. | Either party cancels. | Final state. |
| no_show | Customer did not arrive. | Artist marks no-show. | Final state. |
| expired | Deposit deadline passed. Slot released. | Background job. | Final state. |

*Note: Slot holding race condition: two customers simultaneously trying to hold the same slot — first write wins at database level via GIST exclusion constraint. Second customer receives immediate slot unavailable response. No application-level queue needed.*

## 8.2 Multiple Bookings per Session

- Customer can book multiple services in one session.

- Each booking has its own approval and deposit flow independently.

- Deposit is per service. Each service has its own deposit amount.

## 8.3 Special Requests Field

- Every booking has a free-text special requests field.

- Customer uses it for: color preferences, hair length, skin type, extension type, number of additional persons, Wish Money transaction reference, any other need.

- For complex services, staff calls the customer after booking to confirm details before approving.

## 8.4 Outside Store: Additional Persons

| **Location** | **Base covers** | **Additional person fee (Rania default)** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Home visit inside Lebanon | 1 person | +$300 per person. Configurable per artist. |
| Outside Lebanon | 1 person | +$500 per person. Configurable per artist. |

## 8.5 Reimbursable Expenses (Outside Lebanon)

- Total cost: $2,000 service fee + additional persons fees + sum of all actual expenses.

- Expense types: hotel, transportation, visa fees, other.

- Added by artist as line items before or after the trip.

- Customer notified when expenses are added and shown the updated total.

- UI for adding expenses ships in Phase 1 for Rania. Full expense management UI in Phase 2.

# 9. Scheduling Rules

## 9.1 Operating Hours

| **Rule** | **Beirut default** | **Tripoli default** | **Configurable** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Opening time | Configurable | Configurable | Yes per store |
| Closing time | 6pm | 6pm | Yes per store |
| Early bird cutoff | Before 9am | Before 7:30am | Yes per store |
| Early bird fee | Configurable | Configurable | Yes per store |
| Full makeup from | 11am | 11am | Yes per service |
| Same-day minimum notice | 4 hours | 4 hours | Yes per store |
| Holidays and blackout dates | Configurable per store | Configurable per store | Yes per store |

*Note: Business hours exceptions: Each store can define holiday closures and blackout dates. These are stored in the business_hours_exceptions table and take precedence over regular operating hours.*

## 9.2 Multi-Store Travel Buffer

| **Day type** | **Default buffer** | **Example** | **Configurable** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Weekdays (Mon-Thu) | 2.5 hours (150 min) | Tripoli ends 9:10am. Earliest Beirut: 11:40am. | Yes per artist per store pair |
| Weekends (Fri-Sun) | 1.5 hours (90 min) | Tripoli ends 9:10am. Earliest Beirut: 10:40am. | Yes per artist per store pair |

- Buffer applies in BOTH directions before and after any cross-store booking.

- Example reverse: Beirut starts 8am weekday. Tripoli slots before 6:30am are blocked.

- Two stores in the same city can have a shorter buffer (e.g. 30 minutes).

- For international travel, buffer calculated per trip.

- Store-only artists never appear in other stores availability.

## 9.3 Service Duration and Processing Gap

- System validates: start time + service duration must not exceed store closing time.

- Rejected bookings show the latest valid start time for that service.

- Services with processing gaps: artist is free during the processing window for another client. System blocks the chair but not the artist.

- Home visit and outside Lebanon: no closing time validation.

## 9.4 Rescheduling

- Artist can reschedule a single booking to a new time.

- Artist can bulk reschedule all bookings on a day by a time offset.

- Bulk reschedule returns moved list and failed list. Partial success allowed.

- Cascading conflicts detected before committing. Full chain shown to artist.

- Customer notified automatically of any reschedule.

- Artist reschedule always triggers full deposit refund to customer.

## 9.5 Waitlist

- Customer joins waitlist for a fully booked slot.

- Notification goes to the first in queue when a slot opens.

- Notified customer gets a configurable window (e.g. 30 minutes) to confirm before next in line is notified.

- No time limit on waitlist entry duration.

- Customer can waitlist multiple services simultaneously.

- Waitlist entry has no deposit. Deposit only required after confirmation.

# 10. Notifications

All notifications are sent asynchronously. The booking transaction always commits first. A background worker sends notifications after. If WhatsApp is down, the booking still succeeds. Notifications never block a transaction.

## 10.1 Notification Events

| **Event** | **Channel** | **Recipient** | **Timing** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Booking received | WhatsApp + app | Artist | Immediately |
| Booking approved | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Immediately. Includes deposit deadline. |
| Deposit reminder | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Configurable. Default: 24 hours before deadline. |
| Booking confirmed (deposit paid) | WhatsApp + SMS | Both | Immediately. |
| Appointment reminder | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Configurable. Default: 24 hours before appointment. |
| Appointment reminder | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Configurable. Default: 2 hours before appointment. |
| Booking cancelled by artist | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Immediately. Includes refund notice. |
| Booking rescheduled by artist | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Immediately. Shows new time. |
| Booking expired (deposit not paid) | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Immediately on expiry. |
| Refund due | App dashboard | Artist | Immediately on cancellation qualifying for refund. |
| Refund completed | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | When artist marks refund sent. |
| Waitlist slot available | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Immediately on slot opening. |
| Product order placed | WhatsApp + app | Artist | Immediately. |
| Product order confirmed | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | Immediately. |
| Product order shipped | WhatsApp + SMS | Customer | When artist marks shipped. |

## 10.2 Notification Reliability

- WhatsApp is primary channel. SMS is automatic fallback if WhatsApp delivery fails.

- Retry policy: 3 attempts with exponential backoff (1 min, 5 min, 15 min).

- Dead-letter queue: notifications that fail all 3 attempts are moved to failed status and flagged for manual review.

- Deduplication: same notification cannot be sent twice to the same user for the same event within a 5-minute window.

- Customer opt-out: customers can set notification preferences (which events they receive, which channels).

- Template versioning: notification templates are versioned in the database. Changes do not affect in-flight notifications.

- All notification timing is configurable per salon.

# 11. Security

Security requirements validated against OWASP API Security Top 10 and industry best practices. Full technical implementation details are in the companion document: B-Edge Technical Decisions and Engineering Principles v1.

| **Area** | **Requirement** | **Implementation** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Passwords | bcrypt hashed. Never stored plain. | Cost 10 in production. Cost 1 in tests. |
| JWT secrets | 64+ random hex chars minimum. | Validated on startup. Fails fast if too short. |
| Token expiry | Access: 15 minutes. Refresh: 7 days. | httpOnly cookie for refresh token. Never in JS. |
| Token rotation | New refresh token on every /refresh call. | Old token invalidated immediately. |
| Email enumeration | Wrong email returns same message as wrong password. | Timing-safe comparison. |
| Rate limiting | 100 requests per 15 minutes per IP on all /api/ routes. | Configurable. Applied on all endpoints. |
| Input validation | Every endpoint validated before business logic runs. | go-playground/validator v10. |
| SQL injection | Parameterized queries everywhere. Never string interpolation. | pgx parameterized queries. |
| Multi-tenant isolation | salon_id always from JWT. Never from request body. | Enforced in service layer via context. |
| CORS | Whitelist only. CLIENT_URL env var. | Fiber CORS middleware. |
| Data in transit | HTTPS only in production. SSL via Let's Encrypt. | Nginx reverse proxy. |
| Audit access | audit_events readable by Owner only for their salon. | Role check on audit log endpoints. |

# 12. Non-Functional Requirements

Minimum targets for launch on AWS EC2 t3.medium. These gate infrastructure decisions. All targets are for the Lebanese market at launch scale.

| **Requirement** | **Target** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Availability query response time | < 300ms p95 | Artist availability for a given date and store. |
| Booking creation response time | < 500ms p95 | Includes hold creation and conflict check. |
| API response time (general) | < 200ms p95 | For all non-availability endpoints. |
| Concurrent users at launch | 50 simultaneous | Rania's customer base at launch. Scales horizontally on K8s. |
| Uptime SLA | 99.5% monthly | Maximum 3.6 hours downtime per month. |
| Database read/write ratio | Estimated 80% reads, 20% writes | Read replicas added when needed in Phase 3. |
| Background job frequency | Every 1 minute | Expired hold cleanup, deposit deadline checks. |

