## 13.2 Order State Machine

| **Status** | **Meaning** | **Next states** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| placed | Customer placed order. Awaiting salon confirmation. | confirmed, cancelled |
| confirmed | Salon confirmed. Preparing order. | shipped, cancelled |
| shipped | Handed to courier. In transit. | delivered, returned |
| delivered | Customer received. | Final state. |
| cancelled | Cancelled by customer or salon. | Final state. |
| returned | Customer returned order. | Final state. |

# 14. Features Roadmap

## 14.1 Phase 1: Launch

| **Feature** | **Description** | **Industry reference** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Online booking 24/7 | Customer PWA. Any service, artist, store. | Fresha, Vagaro standard |
| Real-time availability | Per artist per store. Travel buffers. Processing gaps. | Standard + B-Edge extensions |
| Custom services | Any salon adds custom services beyond the catalogue. | Vagaro, Square custom service model |
| Staff roles and permissions | 5 roles. Hub-and-spoke. Location-level permissions. | Fresha 5-level model |
| Booking approval + deposit | Artist approves. Customer pays deposit. Confirmed. | Fresha, Vagaro configurable deposit |
| Slot holding during checkout | 10-minute hold. First-write-wins at DB level. | Airbnb held status pattern |
| Deposit verification (manual) | Rania marks deposit received. Customer sees status. | B-Edge manual flow |
| Multiple bookings per session | Book multiple services. Per-service deposit. | Fresha group bookings |
| Special requests field | Free text. Staff callback for complex services. | Vagaro client notes |
| Processing gap support | Artist free during kreatin / color development. | Boulevard, GlossGenius |
| Outside store surcharge | Additional persons charged per person. | B-Edge unique feature |
| WhatsApp + SMS notifications | Async. Configurable timing. Retry policy. Opt-out. | B-Edge WhatsApp for MENA |
| Notification reliability | Retry 3x, dead-letter queue, deduplication, templates. | B-Edge notification reliability spec |
| Cancellation policy | 24hr window enforced automatically. | Vagaro, GlossGenius no-show protection |
| Refund tracking queue | Artist sees pending refunds. Customer sees status. | B-Edge manual flow |
| Discounts and promotions | Percentage, fixed, promo codes, seasonal. | Fresha, Vagaro promotional tools |
| Waitlist | Queue-based notification when slot opens. | Fresha intelligent waitlist |
| Business hours exceptions | Holidays and blackout dates per store. | Industry standard |
| Multi-store + travel buffer | Weekday and weekend buffers per artist. | B-Edge unique feature |
| Artist onboarding | Self-service. Catalogue or custom services. | Fresha, Vagaro self-service |
| Customer profiles | History, favourites, refund status. | Vagaro detailed profiles |
| Product store | Optional. Sell products. Cash on delivery. | Vagaro, Square retail module |
| Audit log | Append-only. Every financial and status action. | Financial system best practice |
| Admin dashboard | Owner sees all stores, staff, bookings, refund queue. | Hub-and-spoke industry standard |
| Arabic RTL interface | Full Arabic in both PWAs. | B-Edge MENA differentiator |

## 14.2 Phase 2: Growth (Month 2 to 3)

| **Feature** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| Client intake forms | Customizable per service. Allergies, skin type, previous treatments. GlossGenius Genius Forms model. |
| Instagram integration | Artist portfolio linked from Instagram. |
| Client notes and history | Treatment notes per client visible before appointment. |
| Referral programme | Customer refers friend. Both get discount. |
| Rebooking reminders | Remind clients to rebook after configurable weeks. |
| SMS marketing | Artist sends campaigns to client list. |
| Course management | Full participant list management for class courses. |
| Full expense management UI | Add and track outside-Lebanon reimbursable expenses. |
| Repeat no-show policy | Auto-require deposit from clients with multiple no-shows. |
| Product store enhancements | Discounts, featured products, product reviews. |
| Ramadan seasonal pricing | Time-limited pricing windows for peak demand. MENA exclusive. |
| WhatsApp booking bot | Handle booking requests conversationally via WhatsApp. |
| Reviews and ratings | Public ratings on artist profiles. Moderation workflow. |

## 14.3 Phase 3: Expansion (Month 6+)

| **Feature** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| Open platform | Any salon or artist in Lebanon can register. |
| Online payments | Stripe or regional gateway. Replaces Wish Money. Enables online product payment. |
| Automated refunds | Refunds via payment gateway. No manual step. |
| Multi-currency | LBP, SAR, AED, JOD. MENA expansion. |
| Dynamic pricing | Demand-based and time-of-day pricing. Up to 25% occupancy increase. |
| Loyalty programme | Points per booking and purchase. |
| AI scheduling | Smart slot suggestions and team allocation. |
| Analytics dashboard | Revenue, peak hours, top services, no-show rates, top products. |
| MENA expansion | Jordan, UAE, KSA. |
| White label | Salons operate B-Edge under their own brand. |

# 15. Database Schema

Technical implementation details — indexes, constraints, migration rules — are in the companion document: B-Edge Technical Decisions and Engineering Principles v1.

| **Table** | **Key fields** | **Purpose** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| users | id UUID, name, email, password_hash, role, phone, status, created_at, deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ | Every person on the platform. |
| salons | id UUID, name, owner_id FK users, created_at | A beauty business. One owner, many stores and staff. |
| stores | id UUID, salon_id, name, city, country, open_time, close_time, same_day_booking_enabled, min_advance_hours | A physical location. Operating hours and booking rules per store. |
| business_hours_exceptions | id UUID, store_id, date DATE, is_closed BOOLEAN, open_time, close_time, reason, created_at | Holiday closures and exceptional hours overrides per store. |
| salon_staff | id UUID, salon_id, user_id, role (owner/manager/receptionist/artist/assistant) | Staff membership and role per salon. |
| worker_stores | id UUID, user_id, store_id, is_primary | Which stores each artist works at. Many-to-many. |
| artist_travel_buffers | id UUID, artist_id, from_store_id, to_store_id, weekday_buffer_minutes, weekend_buffer_minutes | Travel time between stores per artist. Weekday and weekend separately. |
| service_categories | id UUID, salon_id, name, is_custom BOOLEAN, display_order | Service categories. Platform defaults and custom salon categories. |
| services | id UUID, artist_id, store_id, salon_id, category_id, name, description, duration_min, processing_gap_minutes, price NUMERIC, currency, deposit_amount NUMERIC, location_type, available_from TIME, outside_per_person_fee NUMERIC, includes TEXT[], requires_consultation BOOLEAN, is_custom BOOLEAN, template_id UUID, is_active, created_at, deleted_at | Service offered by artist at store. Custom or catalogue. |
| bookings | id UUID, customer_id, artist_id, service_id, store_id, salon_id, date DATE, start_time TIMESTAMPTZ, end_time TIMESTAMPTZ, status, held_until TIMESTAMPTZ, deposit_amount NUMERIC, deposit_paid_at, deposit_method, deposit_deadline TIMESTAMPTZ, approved_at, approved_by, additional_persons, cancellation_reason, discount_applied, refund_status, refund_amount, refunded_at, special_requests, created_at, deleted_at | Central transactional table. Every appointment. |
| booking_expenses | id UUID, booking_id, type (hotel/transport/visa/other), description, amount NUMERIC, currency, created_at | Reimbursable expenses for outside Lebanon bookings. |
| waitlist | id UUID, artist_id, store_id, service_id, customer_id, date, time, requested_at, notified_at, notified_until TIMESTAMPTZ, expires_at, status | Waitlist queue per slot. |
| reviews | id UUID, booking_id UNIQUE, customer_id, artist_id, rating INTEGER (1-5), comment, is_visible BOOLEAN, created_at | One review per completed booking. Phase 2 visibility and moderation. |
| discounts | id UUID, artist_id, salon_id, type, value NUMERIC, code, scope, valid_from, valid_until, max_uses, uses_count, is_active | Promotional discounts. |
| early_bird_fees | id UUID, store_id, before_time TIME, fee_amount NUMERIC | Early bird surcharge configuration per store. |
| audit_events | id UUID, entity_type, entity_id, action, old_value JSONB, new_value JSONB, performed_by, source (app/admin/system/background), created_at TIMESTAMPTZ | Append-only. Every status change and financial action. Retention: 7 years. |
| notifications | id UUID, user_id, type, channel (whatsapp/sms/email), status (pending/sent/failed/dead_letter), attempt_count, payload JSONB, sent_at, created_at | Async notification queue with retry tracking. |
| notification_templates | id UUID, salon_id, event_type, channel, language, template_body, version INTEGER, is_active, created_at | Versioned notification templates per salon per language. |
| notification_preferences | id UUID, user_id, event_type, channel, is_enabled, updated_at | Customer opt-out preferences per event and channel. |
| course_bookings | id UUID, booking_id, course_type (private/class), participants TEXT[], price_per_person NUMERIC, max_participants INTEGER | Course booking data. |
| products | id UUID, salon_id, category_id, name, description, price NUMERIC, stock_count, is_active, created_at, deleted_at | Product store catalogue. |
| product_categories | id UUID, salon_id, name, display_order | Product categories per salon. |
| product_images | id UUID, product_id, url, cloudinary_id, display_order | Product photos via Cloudinary. |
| product_orders | id UUID, customer_id, salon_id, status, delivery_address, total_amount NUMERIC, payment_method (cash_on_delivery), notes, created_at | Product orders. |
| product_order_items | id UUID, order_id, product_id, quantity, unit_price NUMERIC, subtotal NUMERIC | Line items per order. |
| media | id UUID, owner_id, owner_type (artist/salon/service/product), url, cloudinary_id, type (photo/video), display_order, created_at | All media assets. Artist portfolio, service photos, product images. |
| password_resets | id UUID, user_id, token VARCHAR UNIQUE, expires_at TIMESTAMPTZ, used_at, created_at | Forgot password tokens. 1 hour expiry. |

*Note: Cloudinary handles all media: artist profiles, service photos, portfolio, and product images. All tables use UUID v4 primary keys, TIMESTAMPTZ for all timestamps, NUMERIC(10,2) for all money, and soft delete with deleted_at. See Technical Decisions document for full indexing and constraint specifications.*

# 16. Glossary

| **Term** | **Definition** |
| --- | --- |
| Layliye (ليليه) | The night before the wedding celebration. A Lebanese and Levantine tradition. Guests gather the evening before the wedding for music, dancing, and festivities. Bride gets special makeup for this event. |
| Sahra (سهرة) | Evening or party occasion. A woman going to a dinner, concert, or social event. Distinct makeup service type between daily and engagement. Common occasion type in Lebanese salons. |
| Khitbe (خطبة) | Engagement ceremony. Formal occasion where the couple announces their engagement. One of the major beauty booking occasions. |
| Henna night (ليلة الحنة) | Pre-wedding celebration featuring henna body art. Common across Lebanon, GCC, and MENA. Separate beauty event requiring makeup and hair styling. |
| Hawajeb (حواجب) | Eyebrow shaping and grooming service. One of the most frequently booked services in Lebanese salons. Can be done by threading, waxing, or razor. |
| Kreatin | Keratin hair smoothing and strengthening treatment. Applied and processed over 1 to 3 hours. The processing time creates a scheduling gap where the artist is free. |
| Wish Money | Lebanese digital payment platform. The primary deposit payment method for B-Edge at launch before online payment integration. |
| PWA | Progressive Web App. A web application that behaves like a native mobile app. B-Edge uses PWA for both the customer and artist interfaces. |
| GIST constraint | PostgreSQL Generalized Search Tree exclusion constraint. Used to prevent double booking at the database level. Enforces that no two confirmed bookings can overlap in time for the same artist. |
| Keyset pagination | A pagination technique that uses the last seen record as a cursor instead of an offset. Equally fast for any page number regardless of dataset size. |
| Travel buffer | Blocked time around a cross-store booking to account for travel time between locations. Configurable per artist per store pair with separate values for weekdays and weekends. |
| Processing gap | Time during a service where the artist is not actively working on the client. For example during kreatin processing or hair color development. Artist can take another client during this window. |
| Held status | Temporary booking status during checkout. Slot is reserved for 10 minutes while the customer completes the booking form. Prevents the slot from being taken by another customer simultaneously. |
| Dead-letter queue | A queue for notifications that have failed all retry attempts. Flagged for manual review rather than silently discarded. |

